<br>
There has needed to be a central trading zone for a long time. They bazaar fits that bill perfect since it ain't hard to get to and no one team controls it. <br>
<br>
I'm mean the way it goes right now I'm having to go back and fourth between GFay and EC to make any decent trades. While it's fun to be sneaking around in enemy territory wondering if I'm gonna have to kill some stupid evil who dares test me. I'm not opposed to the idea of doing my trading and getting back to leveling or pk'ing.<br>
<br>
Now the Nexus being non-pvp I'm kinda surprised about, but I see why they did it that way. Portal camping would take on a whole new meaning. Entire guilds would be there fighting constantly. Might be fun for a while, but sometimes you just wanna go to da moon =)<br>
<br>
